Captured at the Carrier Dome in Syracuse, NY on March 30, 1985. Wayne Shorter Celebration 1/5/2019 Replay
extra: Recorded Saturday, January 5, 2019 at the SFJAZZ Center in San Francisco. Legendary saxophonist and composer Wayne Shorter had been scheduled to perform with his quartet over four nights in the SFJAZZ Center’s Miner Auditorium in January of 2019, but an illness kept Wayne from appearing in San Francisco. In only a few days notice, a tribute to Wayne was put together of all-star roster of artists to perform classic Wayne Shorter material. Saxophonist Kamasi Washington and multi-instrumentalist Terrace Martin join Wayne’s longtime quartet including pianist Danilo Pérez, bassist John Patitucci, and drummer Brian Blade.

extra:
Jazz Foundation Musicians’ Emergency Fund Concert 5/14 Featuring: Sheryl Crow, Robert Cray, Milton Nascimento, Anjelique Kidjo, Stanley Jordan, Ivan Neville and many more.                     
                        In demanding times, musicians keep us grounded. They call up the strong, beautiful parts of our spirits. But without a single gig taking place during this crisis, there are no clubs to go to, no concerts to attend. The sudden standstill has left thousands of vulnerable artists in a state of financial free fall as they live gig to gig and month to month. The need is unprecedented but reminds us of mission and purpose to provide emergency assistance in time of crisis.
